2. Enter a while loop that continues until the pointers reach the end of the strings or the current characters are different.
3. If the current characters are the same, increment the pointers i and j to move to the next character.
4. If the current characters are different, check if the strings s and t have the same length.
5. If the strings have the same length, replace the character at position i in s with the character at position j in t to make them the same.
6. If the strings do not have the same length, check if the character at position i in s is the same as the character at position j in t.
7. If the characters are the same, delete the character at position j in t to make the strings the same.
8. If the characters are different, insert the character at position j in t into s to make the strings the same.
9. If the strings are still different after the while loop, return False.

